text: Sir Arthur Henry McMahon (1862-1949) was the British chief commissioner in Baluchistan from 1907 to 1908 and from 1909 to 1911. From 1915 to 1917, during World War I, he was the British high commissioner in Egypt. == References == Category:1862 births Category:1949 deaths Category:British Indian Army officers Category:Colonial officials of British India
title: Henry McMahon
